---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Confidence & Self-Worth · Ennea Evolution"
  description="There's a life you want. Something keeps telling you you're not the one who gets to have it. Confidence is a skill, and it's learnable."
>
  <div style="--accent:#B22B2E;">
    <!-- PANEL 1 · white · hero -->
    <section class="panel">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Personal Work</p>
        <h1>There's a life you want. Something keeps telling you you're not the one who gets to have it.</h1>
        <p class="lead">Maybe you keep not asking, not applying, not starting the thing, because a quiet voice says <em>it won't work</em>, or <em>you're not ready</em>, or <em>who do you think you are</em>.</p>
        <p>Or maybe you already do plenty. You succeed, perform, prove. And none of it quite lands. The win fades by morning, and the question of whether you're enough wakes back up.</p>
        <p>Different on the surface. The same question underneath: <em>Can I trust myself to be okay?</em></p>
        <p>You can, and it's learnable. Confidence isn't a personality some people are born with. It's a skill, and I've watched people build it many times.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 2 · tint #F2CFC5 · inner voice -->
    <section class="panel tint-band" style="--tint:#F2CFC5;">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>You might recognize this</h3>
        <div class="inner-voice" style="margin-bottom:-1.5rem;">
          <p>I talk myself out of things before I've even let myself want them.</p>
          <p>The praise rolls right off me. The one sharp comment stays for a week.</p>
          <p>Everyone seems so sure I can do this. I'm still waiting for the evidence.</p>
          <p>I'll do it when I feel ready. I've been saying that for years.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 3 · white -->
    <section class="panel">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>Why "just be confident" has never worked</h3>
        <p>The doubt rarely feels like a problem. It feels practical, sensible, humble. But it's been quietly running the show, and it doesn't respond to logic, because what you believe about yourself was never reasoned into place. That's why one more accomplishment doesn't settle it.</p>
        <p>The part of you that keeps you small isn't broken. At some point it made complete sense, and it's been doing a job ever since. When you see why, its grip starts to loosen, and you get a real say in what happens next.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">What the work is</h3>
        <p>We build the thing underneath confidence: the ability to move before you're sure. You let yourself want things out loud. You take the step while the doubt is still talking. And every time you come through the not-knowing intact, the trust grows.</p>
        <blockquote class="pullquote">What we're after isn't the belief that everything will work out. It's something sturdier: trusting that you'll be okay even if it doesn't.</blockquote>
        <div class="photo-block" style="--block:#F2CFC5; margin-top:2.5rem;">
          <div class="photo">
            <img src="/img/confidence-stand.jpg" alt="A woman standing tall, chin up, self-assured in the open air" width="1400" height="966" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">What changes</h3>
        <p>You start moving while the doubt talks, because its vote no longer decides. When something goes well, it lands. When something goes badly, it doesn't become the whole story about you.</p>
        <p>You rest without earning it. You want things without apologizing for wanting them. And the life that felt like it belonged to other people starts looking like one you're allowed to reach for.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="hairline-gold" />

    <!-- PANEL 4 · white · close -->
    <section class="panel center">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>Start here</h3>
        <p>You don't have to feel brave yet. Just a little tired of standing still. Bring the thing you keep not reaching for.</p>
        <a href="/get-started" class="btn" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Schedule a Free 15-Minute Call</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
